[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two face Bowker Vale tram stop assault charges

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two 17-year-old boys have appeared at youth court charged with assaulting a Jewish boy at a Manchester tram stop.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Moshe Fuerst, 17, suffered a fractured skull after an attack at Bowker Vale Metrolink station on Saturday night.
He required surgery to remove a blood clot on the brain after what police described as an anti-Semitic attack.
The boys, who cannot be identified, have been charged with actual bodily harm, common assault and affray.
One of the boys has also been charged with grievous bodily harm.
Police said no further action will be taken against a third 17-year-old boy who was arrested in connection with the incident.
